Le 09/06/2015 17:53, Carles Gomez Montenegro a écrit :
> Hi Alex,
>
>>>> Is IPv6 running over BTLE?
>>>
>>> Yes, several companies have implemented it, including Nordic
>>> (http://www.nordicsemi.com/eng/News/News-releases/Product-Related-News/Nordic-Semiconductor-IPv6-over-Bluetooth-Smart-protocol-stack-for-nRF51-Series-SoCs-enables-small-low-cost-ultra-low-power-Internet-of-Things-applications).
>>
>> That announcement says "IPv6/BluetoothSmart".    Bluetooth Smart
>> comprises classic Bluetooth and BTLE.
>
> No:
>
>>From the IPv6 over BLE draft, section 2, 1st paragraph:
>
>     "Bluetooth Special Interest Group (Bluetooth SIG) has introduced two
>     trademarks, Bluetooth Smart for single-mode devices (a device that
>     only supports Bluetooth LE) and Bluetooth Smart Ready for dual-mode
>     devices (devices that support both Bluetooth and Bluetooth LE).  In
>     the rest of the document, the term Bluetooth LE refers to both types
>     of devices."

That paragraph of the document is confusing for a couple of reasons.

Is the term Bluetooth LE referring to both single-mode devices and 
dual-mode devices?  Or is it referring to both Bluetooth and to 
Bluetooth LE devices?

The second reason of confusion is that it may try to specify 
IPv6/Bluetooth behaviour which is wrong.  IPv6/Bluetooth does not use HC.

Maybe that paragraph above should be clarified.

>> Which part is that company implementing:"IP/classicBluetooth" or
>> "IP/BTLE"?  Since we agreed that these are two different things we would
>> also agree these are two different concepts: "IP/classicBT" and "IP/BTLE".
>>
>> For that reason, again - is there a packet dump exhibiting IPv6/BTLE w/
>> HC?  That would help clarify to me some things that may be obvious,
>> thanks.
>
> I don't have such a packet dump available, sorry.

Maybe we can ask a member of the 6lo group to provide us a packet dump 
of IPv6/BluetoothLE so we can understand better.

Alex

>
> Regards,
>
> Carles
