Hi Randy,

Turner, Randy wrote:
> DHCP configuration of RFC 6282 compression contexts

RFC 6282 compression contexts need to be identical between each pair of
compressing and decompressing nodes, i.e., throughout the LoWPAN.  RFC
6775 provides a way to disseminate this information that is relatively
robust in this respect; there is also a discussion about the life cycle
considerations that apply here in Section 7.2 of RFC 6775.
A quick scan of the new draft does not yield answers to the obvious
questions:
-- how is the consistency throughout the LoWPAN ensured?
-- how are life cycles managed?

Actually, I would like to have additional information about why you
think that DHCP is a better way to manage compression context
information than the mechanisms provided in RFC 6775.

