Hi Alex,

> Le 09/06/2015 13:55, Carles Gomez Montenegro a écrit :
>> Hi Alex,
>>
>> Do you have any news on any Bluetooth SIG plans to create some version
>> of
>> BLE that can be compatible with classic Bluetooth?
>
> Here is some news: Bluetooth 4.2 seems to be offering a procedure to
> negotiate larger data packets ("LE Data Packet Length Extension")
> (instead of currently 27 bytes).  If that materializes can it be assumed
> that Header Compression for IPv6 be less necessary when running IPv6/BTLE?
>
> Alex

Just to avoid possible confusion: those 'news' are not related with my
original question above. That is, Bluetooth 4.2 is *not* a move to making
Bluetooth LE "backwards compatible" with classic Bluetooth.

Regarding your question, you always have energy and throughput gains by
using header compression. If the involved packets are 'large', the
benefits are lower in relative terms than with 'short' packets, but there
are still benefits.

Regards,

Carles


