Hi Carles,

Yes, I respectfully exchange messages with you, and copy the list.

Please, respectfully, do not forward me outside this discussion.  I 
already make part of several discussions outside this thread on the same 
topic.

Also, when forwarding me, if absolutely necessary, please point me to 
specific phrases or paragraphs.  E.g. which part of the shepherd 
writeup, because some parts of it are wrong and I dont have time to 
discuss them.  And yes many parts of the shepherd writeup are very good 
and correct.

I _can_ spend much time to read code, exercice experiments, read packet 
dumps.

My comments are about reflecting implementation status into documents. 
If we do have deployment of IPv6/BTLE then reflect it.  If we dont have 
deployment of IPv6/BTLE then dont try to pretend it, because there are 
other competitors taking it already.

BTLE is integral part of Bluetooth 4.0 and onwards.

BTLE-only devices are incompatible with Bluetooth-only devices.

Laptops and smartphones are equipped with dual-mode interfaces which 
offer a single interface to IP.

BTLE deployments I am aware of (except one demo) dont use IP.

IPv6 is not part at all of any Bluetooth spec.

