I would not put it that broad, but in a sense yes.

In the current Internet everyone can talk to other.  But an IPv6/BTLE
node as per this document can not talk to an IPv6/BT in the same subnet,
because of that HC.

Without talking HC: IP can not solve a link layer problem.

The fact that interfaces are declared both BT and BTLE, yet BT and BTLE 
are incompatible is a huge link layer problem.  But it is not IP's problem.

IP can connect together heterogeneous links by means of routing.  These 
means are specified, exist.  Yet IPv6/BTLE does not want to talk 
Bluetooth-classic.

> Do you imply that 6LoWPAN (e.g. over IEEE 802.15.4)

