BT and BTLE: BTLE is not BT, and IPv6 runs ok over BT w/o HC).

> breaks the current architecture of the Internet?

I imply that 6lowpan is an adaptation layer that is not adapting things
as it is need by IP.  Other adaptation layers do its job such that IP 
runs over these links in a very simple and straighforward manner.

