some IP perspective there is no energy limitation.

A watch is limited in energy, yes, (run on CR2032), but it is so limited
that it does not run IP.  It does not need it, and IP is a hurdle for
it: operators dont give a /63 to a smartphone, and IETF doesnt allow
shorter IIDs than 64.

For that reason - everyone is happy with current situation: energy
limitation?  No need of IP.  IP is not a panacea where a bigger battery
would do the trick.

