> the BT SIG has contributed to.

I can agree, but I think it's up to the BT SIG to design non-IP matters
and up to IETF to design IP matters.

> Production quality implementations have since been done.  There is
> absolutely nothing EXPERIMENTAL about this.

Ok, but,

The implementation of this draft uses addressing architecture which is
INFORMATIONAL: extracting the address for a BTLE device from a /64
prefix allocated by the cellular operator is specified in RFC7274
"Extending an IPv6 /64 Prefix from a Third Generation Partnership
Project (3GPP) Mobile Interface to a LAN Link" INFORMATIONAL.

IPv6 works over Bluetooth 4.0 (whose specs include BTLE) without using
this draft, and that is in wide public deployment (bluez).  That should
be Stds Track, and not this draft.

The implementations of this draft are not publicly available, dumps are
not available, etc.

