> Hi Alex,
>
> Let us focus on the draft reviewing.
>
> The draft has  clear  abstract about the  versioning and purpose of
> this specification.
>
> Also, this is a standard track document--  it has been implemented,
> reviewed by many  and this specification is important for moving
> 6lowpan/IPv6 deployment on BTLE.

But it is more important to not break existing IPv6/Bluetooth 
deployments.  IPv6/BTLE is incompatible with IPv6/Bluetooth deployments.

> For any future extensions to this solution can be  added and
> specified later like any other standards specification process at
> IETF.

I am not asking feature extensions.  I am saying that this IPv6/BTLE is 
putting the cart (IPv6/BTLE) before the horse (IPv6/Bluetooth 4.0).

An IPv6/Bluetooth4.0 computer pings ok an IPv6/Bluetooth2.0, whereas an 
IPv6/BTLE-only cant. BTLE spec is part of Bluetooth 4.0, but not part of 
Bluetooth 2.0.

It is IPv6/Bluetooth4.0 that should prime, and the incompatible 
IPv6/BTLE-only should be EXPERIMENTAL.

Unfortunately we dont have an IPv6/Bluetooth4.0 Internet Draft.  I guess 
because there is not much to put in it.  The things are so simple that 
people may not find it worth documenting.  But that is what is deployed 
and compatible, backwards compatible, compatible with good Internet 
connections, open source available, etc.

I can sketch the lines of such IPv6/Bluetooth4.0 draft if there is interest.

Alex



