> On Jun 17, 2015, at 19:44, Kerry Lynn <kerlyn@ieee.org> wrote:
>=20
> Recommend rewriting these sentences as follows: =E2=80=9CLoBAC is a =
subset of the LoWPAN encapsulation defined in RFC 4944 and extended in =
RFC 6282, therefore the use of =E2=80=9CLOWPAN=E2=80=9D in the literals =
below is intentional. The principle difference between LoBAC and LoWPAN =
are the omission of the Fragmentation, Mesh, Broadcast and LOWPAN_HC1 =
headers.
>=20
> I will go back and review this again, but I don't see a need to =
support HC1 compression.

I don=E2=80=99t mean to suggest 6LoBAC should support HC1 compression. I =
was merely making an editorial note about the use of the word =
=E2=80=9Cdeprecated=E2=80=9D in the current draft. That=E2=80=99s =
unclear terminology, and my recommendation is just to explicitly list =
the LOWPAN_HC1 header as one of the kinds that appears in 6LoWPAN [RFC =
4944] that doesn=E2=80=99t appear in 6LoBAC.

=E2=80=94james=

