> <RCC>
> That may be using the ZEP encapsulation protocol, which wraps like:
>
> EthernetII(EtherType 0x8000)[IPv4[UDP[ZEP[802.15.4]]]]
> </RCC>

Ok.  But this is obviously many headers.

Is there a way to carry 6lowpan packets without involving wrappers?

Wouldnt it be better to do:

802.15.4Header|LLC Header|IPv6BaseHeader
which would further be adapted by an Adaptation Layer towards

EthernetII|IPv6BaseHEader.

In this case, even if the 802.15.4Header does not use an EtherType, the 
LLCHeader does use 0x86dd EtherType for IPv6.  And this EtherType is put 
in the EtherType field of the EthernetII header.

Or it could be:
802.15.4Header|LLC Header|LOWPAN_HC header
with a newly allocated EtherType in the LLC Header.

