The term 'ethertype' is widely used in common conversation to mean very 
particular things.  Ethertypes are under the _control_ of IEEE and for 
historical reasons listed by IANA as well, as an 'echo' if you wish. 
IETF and IANA dont _control_ nor allocate ethertypes.

I am not sure whether tcpdump's linktype means the same thing as 
'ethertype'?  (I never heard of 'linktype'?).

