> address of 0x0000 using a 6LoWPAN context according to RFC6282.</RCC>

Ok, I conflated multicast - sorry, but now SLAAC is conflated into 
discussion.

My point is that there is a relationship between the MAC addresses and 
the IPv6 addresses ("address mapping") which needs to be there.


