>     LLC Header
>     IPv6 Base Header
>     payload
>
>     What do you think?
>
>
> <RCC2>
> That is not right at all. You still seem to be missing the point that
> the EthernetII frame is simply added by the network adapter and is not
> on the wire/ether.

No I dont miss this.  Indeed EthernetII header is simply added by the 
network adapter and is not on the ether.  That's why I said up there "no 
EthernetII".

> You also seem to have lost the 6LoWPAN header which
> is what adapts IPv6 to 802.15.4.

In some cases it is good to adapt IPv6 to 15.4 by involving a 6lowpan 
header.

But I claim in other cases that may be complex compared to simpler and 
has some negative influence on end-to-end reachability, 
neighbor-to-neighbor communicatin, retro-compatibility and security.

> Please take the time to use Wireshark to carefully analyse the packets
