Hello Paul,

Thank you for the offer that should be considered carefully.  I think
the amount does not exceed what may average a in-person participation to
an IETF meeting, so it should be feasible.

I have three comments:

1. does this include definition of a proper LLC header to sit on top of
    15.4DataHeader?  Because, in our understanding, only this LLC may
    carry an EtherType.  A 15.4 DataHeader does not carry an EtherType.

2. is IEEE charging for EtherTypes?  Or is it charging for OUIs?  Or
    both?

3. any request should come via a formal way with a liaison.  A
    discussion on the email list may not be - yet - consensual enough.
    Consensus could be measured by level of adopting documents into RFCs
    on various tracks.

Alex

